addr="staton-winskel-2010"
title="On the expressivity of symmetry in event structures">[staton-winskel-2010]</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>An <fr:em>event structure</fr:em> is defined to be triple <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (E,\mathsf {Con}_{E}, \leq _E\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is a partial order of <fr:em>events</fr:em> partially ordered by the <fr:em>causal dependency relation</fr:em> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\leq _E]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {Con}_{E}\subseteq  \mathcal {P}_{\mathit {fin}}{\mathopen {}\left (E\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> specifies when a finite subset of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>consistent</fr:em>, satisfying the following laws:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>every downset of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is finite;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>every singleton set is consistent;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>any subset of a consistent subset is consistent;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>for any consistent subset <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in \mathsf {Con}_{E}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\leq  e']]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e'\in  x]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\cup {\mathopen {}\left \{e\right \}\mathclose {}}\in \mathsf {Con}_{E}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
